modules.description: Processes a string by iterating over its characters and their positions, applying a folding function that handles both valid Unicode characters and malformed byte sequences. Accepts optional offset and length parameters to process substrings. Used to parse or analyze encoded string data, such as validating UTF-8 sequences or extracting character-level information.

Processes UTF-7 encoded input streams, translating them into Unicode characters while managing memory efficiently and avoiding blocking operations. It handles byte sequences and provides incremental decoding capabilities. Used to process email or legacy data formats that may contain UTF-7 encoded text.

Processes strings by iterating over characters and their positions, handling Unicode and malformed data with a folding function. Supports substring processing via offset and length, enabling precise control over encoded data analysis. Key operations include character extraction, validation, and transformation. Examples include parsing UTF-8 sequences, counting specific characters, or extracting metadata from encoded text.
